  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is to compare the maternal and neonatal outcomes in the patients with PPROM who
      are managed at home versus those managed at hospital, half the patients will be managed at
      home and the other half will be managed inpatient.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Now the current practice is to manage patients with PPROM at hospital, however it is not
      known yet whether this practice is better than outpatient management as regard maternal and
      neonatal outcome.

      There is some recent evidence that home management of PPROM is safe for both mother and
      neonate, home management is also more convenient with less expenses.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
